You are implementing `app/api/pipeline/render/run/route.ts` for the video pipeline.
This single module exports `POST`, `POST_stitch`, and `GET_status` and wires the `render` pipeline executor.

Requirements
1. Register `registerExecutor("render", ...)` at module load.
2. Executor behavior:
   - Read sections from `loadProject()`.
   - If `params.sections` is a non-empty array, render only matching IDs; otherwise render all sections.
   - Render in batches of `config.render.maxParallelRenders || 1` using `Promise.all` per batch.
   - Output each section to `outputs/sections/{sectionId}.mp4`.
   - Emit section progress events via `send({ type: "section-progress", sectionId, percent })`.
   - After each render, read duration via `getSectionDuration(outputPath)`, then update `project.json`: set that section's `durationSeconds` and recompute cumulative `offsetSeconds` for all sections in order.
   - Serialize project writes through a shared promise chain to avoid races across parallel renders.
3. `POST /api/pipeline/render/run`:
   - Accept optional JSON body `{ sections?: string[] }` (treat invalid/missing as all sections).
   - Start `runPipelineStage("render", { sections }, send)` asynchronously.
   - Stream SSE with `data: <json>\n\n`, emit `{ jobId }` on success, and `{ type: "error", message }` on failure.
   - Return headers: `Content-Type: text/event-stream`, `Cache-Control: no-cache`, `Connection: keep-alive`.
4. `POST_stitch` in this same file:
   - Load sections, build `outputs/sections/{sectionId}.mp4` paths, ensure `outputs/` exists, call `stitchFullVideo(...)`, return `{ jobId }` using `randomUUID()`.
   - On failure, log and return 500 `{ error: "Internal Server Error" }`.
5. `GET_status` in this same file:
   - Return `{ sections, fullVideo }`.
   - Section entry shape: `{ sectionId, status: "done" | "missing", duration? }` based on file existence at `outputs/sections/{sectionId}.mp4`.
   - `fullVideo` shape: `{ exists }` plus `{ path, size, duration }` when `outputs/full_video.mp4` exists.
   - On failure, return 500 `{ error: "Internal Server Error" }`.
6. No authentication checks.

Dependencies
- `@/lib/jobs`: `registerExecutor`, `runPipelineStage`
- `@/lib/render`: `renderSection`, `getSectionDuration`, `stitchFullVideo`
- `@/lib/project`: `loadProject`, `saveProject`
- `@/lib/types`: `RenderProgress`, `SseSend`
- `next/server`, `path`, `fs/promises`, `crypto`

Deliverable
- `app/api/pipeline/render/run/route.ts`
